<TITLE> Fourth-class employees seek end to pay disparity </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Oct 17 (bdnews24.com)A platform of fourth-class government employees on Saturday demanded their pay scale ratio at 1:6 by removing all disparities from grades 8 to18 out of 21 grades in the current pay scale. According to the present pay scale, a fourth-class employee gets their pay according to ratio1:11.75 and their proposed pay scale ratio by Pay Commission is 1:9.75. At a news conference in National Press Club, Aroj Ali, president of Bangladesh Fourth Class Government Employees' Association, made the demand. He also asked the government to name MLSS 'Office Assistant', introduce ration system for them, and transfer those working under projects to revenue sector. Vice president Hiron Miah, general secretary Jahangir Alam, joint general secretary Ziaul Alam Zia and orgsnising secretary Emdadul Haque, among others were present at the conference
